{"cursor":"4061","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Purity' (suddha) is an important concept within much of Theravada and Mahayana\nBuddhism, although the implications of the resultant moral purification may be\nviewed differently in the varying traditions. The aim is to purify the\npersonality of the Buddhist practitioner so that all moral and character\ndefilements and defects (kleshas such as anger, ignorance and lust) are wiped\naway and Nirvana can be obtained.\n","linknr":448,"url":"Purity_in_Buddhism","recorded":1362890420,"links":14,"instances":["buddhism","buddhism"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Buddhist views"],"headings":["Theravada Understanding of Purity","Mahayana Understanding of Purity","See also","Sources","Notes"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["kleshas","buddhism"],["kleshas","buddhism"],["ātman","buddhism"]],"members":["ātman","kleshas"],"related":["Theravada","Mahayana","Nirvana","Theravada","Buddhaghosa","Dhamma","Tathagatagarbha","Buddha_nature","Kleshas_(Buddhism)","Kleshas_(Buddhism)","Jonangpa","Dolpopa","Perfection_of_Wisdom","Angulimaliya_Sutra","Ātman_(Buddhism)","Mahayana_Mahaparinirvana_Sutra","Tathāgatagarbha_doctrine","Tathāgatagarbha_Sūtra"]}